  "why": "The paper's mutation mechanism synthesizes adversarial inputs via a CycleGAN-based Adversarial Example Generator (AEG) that produces reconstructed images in continuous (floating-point) form and selects those reconstructions as adversarial examples, but it does not describe any enforcement of serialized input format constraints (e.g., clipping to [0,255], rounding to integers, or saving to standard image formats). There is no discussion or experiment demonstrating that failures induced by these in-memory/continuous perturbations survive serialization to standard image files or that mutations are applied in the same numerical space as the stored format. Therefore, by the metric definitions, the approach mutates/synthesizes inputs in a continuous intermediate representation without enforcing format constraints, which maps to the 'Low' rating.",
